<item>
            <title>[SOCIALFB-42] FacebookErrorHandler will be handle 404 Not Found Error as org.springframework.social.ResourceNotFoundException.</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SOCIALFB-42</link>
                <project id="10607" key="SOCIALFB">Spring Social Facebook</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;as you know, org.springframework.social.facebook.api.impl.FacebookErrorHandler doesn&apos;t handle there 404 Not found error.&lt;br/&gt;
they (404 not found error) still handle by handleUncategorizedError (DefaultResponseErrorHandler.handleError detect and make HttpClientErrorException, and FacebookErrorHandler caught all of exception &amp;amp; translate to UncategorizedApiException)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;it&apos;s harmful if you using spring-social-facebook on your project.&lt;br/&gt;
(that&apos; why i catch UncategorizedApiException and check that&apos;s rootCause is instanceof HttpClientErrorException, and another check HttpStatus is equal to HttpStatus.NOT_FOUND (404), then finally i can do what i want.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and there org.springframework.social.SocialException hierarchy still there. (and i want 404 Not Found Error translate to org.springframework.social.ResourceNotFoundException. no more Uncategorized Exception)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
